# Cloudflare Pages _redirects
# https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/redirects/
#
# Goal: guarantee that /privacy, /terms, /privacy.html, /terms.html serve
# the compliance documents — NOT a SPA fallback to index.html.
#
# Pages normally serves /privacy as /privacy.html automatically when the
# file exists. But if `not_found_handling = single-page-application` is
# ever enabled on the Pages project (which silently routes unknown paths
# to index.html) the explicit 200-status rewrites below bypass it.
#
# Status 200 = "serve this file WITHOUT changing the browser URL".

/privacy         /privacy.html   200
/terms           /terms.html     200
